//! Conformance Phase C6.3 — `ferrotorch-optim` advanced optimizers + utilities.
//!
//! Modules covered (10):
//!   muon, lbfgs, natural_gradient (kfac), ema, swa, grad_accumulator,
//!   grad_scaler, optimizer (ParamGroup/Optimizer trait), foreach_utils,
//!   differentiable.
//!
//! Reference library: `torch == 2.11.0`. Fixtures live in
//! `tests/conformance/fixtures.json`, generated by
//! `scripts/regenerate_optim_advanced_fixtures.py`.
//!
//! ## Layer 2 — fixture-driven tests
//!
//! EMA, SWA, SWALR, GradScaler, GradientAccumulator, differentiable SGD, and
//! foreach_utils are exercised against exact Python-computed reference values.
//!
//! ## Layer 3 — mathematical-property tests
//!
//! Muon (Newton-Schulz orthogonality + quadratic convergence), LBFGS
//! (quadratic + Rosenbrock convergence), and K-FAC (Kronecker factor update
//! arithmetic + convergence) have no PyTorch reference implementation — these
//! are tested via algebraic invariants and convergence bounds documented in
//! the originating papers.
//!
//! ## cascade_skip convention
//!
//! `cascade_skip!(label)` prints a diagnostic and returns early.  It is NOT
//! `#[ignore]` — the test still runs and emits the notice.  Skip targets are
//! features that require a live GPU or a full training loop.

#![allow(
    clippy::cast_possible_truncation,
    clippy::cast_precision_loss,
    clippy::cast_sign_loss,
    clippy::uninlined_format_args,
    clippy::explicit_iter_loop,
    clippy::redundant_else,
    clippy::approx_constant
)]

